 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">says Investopedia</a>,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cin that REITs pool =
together capital from a large number of investors.=E2=80=9D Nobody especial=
ly thinks of large public equity REITs that way these days, I don=E2=80=99t=
 think. EQR is plainly a=C2=A0<em>company</em>, one whose operations includ=
e buying and developing and managing apartment buildings. If you are an equ=
ity fund manager, sure, go ahead, buy EQR. It is a stock that can give you =
exposure to apartment buildings; you are allowed to buy stocks but not apar=
tment buildings. EQR=E2=80=99s big holders include T. Rowe Price and Fideli=
ty, but its biggest holders are Vanguard Group and BlackRock Inc., because =
it is a large and normal enough stock that it is in the S&amp;P 500 index.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s a stock called PSUS. <a href=
