ly expects to be 30 years,=E2=80=9D but it=C2=A0<em>could=C2=A0</em>be a fi=
xed term. The point is that these trades are=C2=A0<em>pretty=C2=A0</em>simi=
lar. They both involve a large upfront payment, followed by fixed amortizin=
g payments over an expected term of decades.<a class=3D"footnote-index" hre=
